ird is a lightweight and flexible web application framework that runs on top of HummingbirdCore. It is designed to require the minimum number of dependencies and makes no use of Foundation."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It provides a router for directing different endpoints to their handlers, middleware for processing requests before they reach your handlers and processing the responses returned and providing custom encoding\/decoding of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Codable"},{"type":"text","text":" objects."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import Hummingbird","","let router = HBRouter()","router.get(\"hello\") { request -> String in","    return \"Hello\"","}","let app = HBApplication(","    router: router,","    configuration: .init(address: .hostname(\"127.0.0.1\", port: 8080))",")","try await app.runService()"]},{"anchor":"Hummingbird-Extensions","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Hummingbird Extensions"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Hummingbird is designed to require the least number of dependencies possible, but this means many features are unavailable to the core libraries. Additional features are provided through extensions. The Hummingbird repository comes with additional modules "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/documentation\/HummingbirdJobs"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/documentation\/HummingbirdXCT"},{"type":"text","text":". The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/documentation\/HummingbirdJobs"},{"type":"text","text":" library provides a framework for pushing work onto a queue to be processed outside of a request (possibly by another server instance). "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/document